0 Both cities, zero ''steamed regret'' \u2014 only sweet returns on investment. Which city are you betting on? Drop your pick \ud83d\udc47 #RealEstate #NorthVsSouth", "city_hint": null, "tags": ["viral", "chennai", "festival", "mumbai"]}','{"media_format": "branded_card", "meme_concept": "", "card_text": "Idli ko bola ''steamed regret'' \ud83d\ude24\nChennai aur Bengaluru ke property returns dekhe kya? \ud83d\udcc8\nWoh toh ''steamed respect'' hai boss.", "trend_hashtag": "#ShashiTharoor", "city_hint": "chennai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "alt_text": "Branded card with a playful split visual \u2014 steaming idlis on one side and a rising Chennai property graph on the other. Overlay text reads: Idli ko bola ''steamed regret'' \ud83d\ude24 Chennai aur Bengaluru ke property returns dekhe kya? \ud83d\udcc8 Woh toh ''steamed respect'' hai boss. Housing.com logo and Chennai buy link at the bottom. Tags: @ShashiTharoor [LOOKUP: ShashiTharoor official Instagram handle]"}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/58dcf57e/instagram_a1f2c3d4.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(182,'06f335c8-805c-4235-86b0-aefa25abc450','c1c24586','twitter','dry_run_06f335c8','dry_run','output/c1c24586/published/twitter_06f335c8.md','2026-05-19 02:27:02.486564',replace('70 ghante kaam, Sunday ko ice cream 🍦\n\n70 ghante grind ke baad — ghar toh aisa deserve karta hai tu jo office se zyada ache lage.\n\nBengaluru mein apna ghar dhundo → housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru','\n',char(10)),'["#No70HourWorkweek", "#Bengaluru", "#WorkLifeBalance"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "anchor_text": "bengaluru", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','70-hour workweek meme flip — even Murthy took a Sunday off. Agar itni mehnat karni hai, toh ghar bhi toh chahiye jahan wapas aane ka mann kare. Career angle works for LinkedIn too.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,5.900000000000000355,18500,285,95,125,2.799999999999999823,2.399999999999999912,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('70-hour workweek bole the. Sunday ko ice cream khaa rahe the. 🍦\nMehnat karo, par ghar bhi aisa ho jahan lautne ka mann kare.','\n',char(10)),'#No70HourWorkweek','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Narayana Murthy and daughter Akshata enjoy ''Corner House'' icecream','The post references the 70-hour workweek debate (likely the Narayana Murthy/L&T controversy) but the trend hook is thin and quickly abandoned. After the opening line ''70 ghante kaam, Sunday ko ice cream'', the post pivots almost immediately into a housing pitch — ''ghar bhi toh aisa chahiye jahan lautne ka mann kare'' is a warm sentiment but it''s a real estate message wearing a trend costume. Compare to the approved RCB examples: ''18 saal se Ee Sala bol rahe the. 18 saal se ghar khareedne ka soch rahe ho?'' — the trend stays alive all the way through the punchline. Here, the trend dies after line one. The phrase ''jahan lautne ka mann kare'' is the kind of soft emotional copy that could appear in any housing ad, any week, with no trend at all. ''Boss bhi ghar jaate hain yaar'' is a decent jab but it''s a throwaway line rather than a sharpened punchline. The result is a post that feels like a housing promo that borrowed a trending hashtag for reach, rather than a trend post that Housing.com crashed naturally.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 5.5, "shareability": 5.0, "hinglish_wit": 6.0, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong hook with relatable wit about work-life balance (70-hour weeks) that resonates with Bengaluru''s startup/IT culture. Emotional appeal is high—aspiration + FOMO combo (boss goes home, why shouldn''t you have a home worth returning to?). Conversational Hindi-English mix increases accessibility. CTA is direct but could be stronger. Hashtag #No70HourWorkweek is timely and searchable. Missing visual asset (no image) limits scroll-stopping power by ~15-20%. Confidence slightly tempered by lack of multimedia.','{"hashtag": "#No70HourWorkweek", "volume": "rising", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Murthy''s ice cream outing sparked memes about his famous ''70-hour workweek'' statement, with netizens humorously pointing out he was taking a break", "creative_hook": "Even the man who said ''70-hour workweek'' took Sunday off for ice cream. \ud83c\udf68\ud83d\ude02 Moral of the story? Even the hardest workers deserve a home they love coming back to. Work hard, live well \u2014 start with the right address. \ud83c\udfe0 #WorkLifeBalance #GharBhiChaiye", "city_hint": "Bengaluru", "tags": ["viral", "celebrity", "bengaluru", "jobs"]}','{"main_tweet": "70 ghante kaam, Sunday ko ice cream \ud83c\udf66\n\nBoss bhi ghar jaate hain yaar.\n\nItni mehnat kar rahe ho \u2014 ghar bhi toh aisa chahiye jahan lautne ka mann kare.\n\nBengaluru mein apna ghar dhundo \u2192 housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "wit", "char_count": 213, "include_image": false, "revision_summary": "Dropped the weak ''Boss bhi ghar jaate hain'' line, kept the 70-hour tension alive into the punchline by making the contrast (office vs. home comfort) the actual joke, and sharpened the pivot so the housing link feels earned rather than bolted on.", "revised": true}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(183,'e8f58cd8-7ca5-4b16-9b3f-c333bb86d9fb','c1c24586','twitter','dry_run_e8f58cd8','dry_run','output/c1c24586/published/twitter_e8f58cd8.md','2026-05-19 02:27:02.489462',replace('Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? 🍦\n\nIconic addresses age like fine ice cream — Bengaluru ke legendary neighbourhoods bhi waise hi timeless hain.\n\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru','\n',char(10)),'["#NarayanaMurthy", "#CornerHouse", "#NammaBengaluru", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "anchor_text": "bengaluru", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Narayana Murthy''s Corner House ice cream moment — iconic addresses age like fine ice cream. Bengaluru ke legendary neighbourhoods bhi waise hi timeless hote hain.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,8.0,18500,142,28,35,1.199999999999999956,1.449999999999999956,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social','Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? 🍦🏡','#NarayanaMurthy','meme_overlay','publish','published','[]','Narayana Murthy and daughter Akshata enjoy ''Corner House'' icecream','This is a solid, well-crafted trend-jack. The Narayana Murthy x Corner House hook is genuinely timely and the wordplay on ''corner'' (Corner House → apna corner) is clever and earns its place. The first line lands well — punchy, Hinglish, emoji-restrained. The second line (''Iconic addresses age like fine ice cream'') is where it slightly loses steam: it''s a nice metaphor but it pivots the post from the trend into a housing message a beat too early, making the second line feel like a brand caption rather than a continuation of the wit. Compared to the approved RCB example (''Tum apna ghar kab jeeto ge?'') which keeps the punchline razor-thin and lets the trend breathe, this post over-explains the connection. The hashtag order is also correct — #NarayanaMurthy leads. No false claims, no corporate speak. Overall this matches the approved examples in craft but doesn''t clearly surpass them.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 8.0, "shareability": 7.5, "hinglish_wit": 8.0, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong hook leveraging Narayana Murthy''s iconic Corner House reference with clever wordplay (''corner'' → property corner). Wit-based hook is effective for Twitter''s audience. Relevance is moderate—Murthy is evergreen but not trending currently. Emotional appeal (aspiration + nostalgia) lands well with Bengaluru property seekers. CTA is implicit but could be stronger. Missing visual asset (image) limits scroll-stopping power. Hashtag strategy is solid but #NarayanaMurthy may attract non-property audience, diluting conversion intent.','{"hashtag": "#NarayanaMurthy", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Infosys founder Narayana Murthy went viral after being spotted enjoying ice cream with daughter Akshata Murty at Bengaluru''s iconic Corner House parlour", "creative_hook": "Billionaire founder. Britain''s First Lady. One iconic Bengaluru ice cream joint. \ud83c\udf68 Some addresses just never get old \u2014 kind of like that Corner House on your bucket list. Speaking of iconic addresses, we''ve got a few in Bengaluru that age even better. \ud83d\ude09 #BengaluruLiving #FindYourCornerHouse", "city_hint": "Bengaluru", "tags": ["celebrity", "bengaluru", "viral", "luxury"]}','{"main_tweet": "Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? \ud83c\udf66\n\nIconic addresses age like fine ice cream \u2014 Bengaluru ke legendary neighbourhoods bhi waise hi timeless hain.\n\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "wit", "char_count": 220, "include_image": false}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(184,'0d697c11-7776-49e4-ba7c-ed3f25d3fcce','c1c24586','twitter','dry_run_0d697c11','dry_run','output/c1c24586/published/twitter_0d697c11.md','2026-05-19 02:27:02.491540',replace('70-hour workweek bole the. Sunday ko ice cream khaa rahe the. 🍦\n\nItni mehnat karo — par ghar bhi toh chahiye jahan wapas aane ka mann kare.\n\nBengaluru mein apna ghar khoijo → https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru','\n',char(10)),'["#No70HourWorkweek", "#WorkLifeBalance", "#Bengaluru"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "anchor_text": "bengaluru", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','70-hour workweek meme flip — even Murthy took a Sunday off. Agar itni mehnat karni hai, toh ghar bhi toh chahiye jahan wapas aane ka mann kare. Career angle works for LinkedIn too.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,7.5,18500,185,42,68,2.100000000000000088,1.649999999999999912,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('70-hour workweek bole the. Sunday ko ice cream khaa rahe the. 🍦\nMehnat karo, par ghar bhi aisa ho jahan lautne ka mann kare.','\n',char(10)),'#No70HourWorkweek','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Narayana Murthy and daughter Akshata enjoy ''Corner House'' icecream','The post rides the ''70-hour workweek'' discourse well — the opening line (''70-hour workweek bole the. Sunday ko ice cream khaa rahe the.'') is a genuinely funny, relatable subversion that earns its place in the trend conversation. The contrast between hustle-culture preaching and Sunday ice cream reality is sharp and very shareable. However, the pivot in line two (''Itni mehnat karo — par ghar bhi toh chahiye jahan wapas aane ka mann kare'') is where the post softens. The phrase ''jahan wapas aane ka mann kare'' is warm but slightly generic — it''s the kind of line any real estate brand could write. It doesn''t carry the same wit or surprise as the opener, so the punchline lands softer than it should. Compared to the approved RCB examples, which maintain the cultural energy all the way through the pivot (''18 saal se Ee Sala bol rahe the → 18 saal se ghar khareedne ka soch rahe ho''), this post''s housing turn is more earnest than clever. The hashtags are also slightly off — #No70HourWorkweek is not the actual trending hashtag; the real discourse lives under the original speaker''s name or a more organic tag, which slightly weakens trend credibility.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 7.5, "shareability": 7.0, "hinglish_wit": 7.5, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong emotional hook (work-life balance tension) with relatable Hindi-English mix resonates with Bengaluru''s young professional demographic. The ice cream detail adds humour and specificity. However, engagement is capped by: (1) lack of visual asset (no image = lower scroll-stop power), (2) moderately fresh but not breaking-news trend, (3) CTA is clear but generic product link lacks urgency/exclusivity. Predicted 1.65% engagement sits in ''good'' range (2-4% benchmark) but doesn''t reach viral due to missing visual hook and limited emotional stakes (no scarcity/FOMO).','{"hashtag": "#No70HourWorkweek", "volume": "rising", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Murthy''s ice cream outing sparked memes about his famous ''70-hour workweek'' statement, with netizens humorously pointing out he was taking a break", "creative_hook": "Even the man who said ''70-hour workweek'' took Sunday off for ice cream. \ud83c\udf68\ud83d\ude02 Moral of the story? Even the hardest workers deserve a home they love coming back to. Work hard, live well \u2014 start with the right address. \ud83c\udfe0 #WorkLifeBalance #GharBhiChaiye", "city_hint": "Bengaluru", "tags": ["viral", "celebrity", "bengaluru", "jobs"]}','{"main_tweet": "70-hour workweek bole the. Sunday ko ice cream khaa rahe the. \ud83c\udf66\n\nItni mehnat karo \u2014 par ghar bhi toh chahiye jahan wapas aane ka mann kare.\n\nBengaluru mein apna ghar khoijo \u2192 https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "wit", "char_count": 211, "include_image": false}',NULL);
