68 Some addresses just never get old \u2014 kind of like that Corner House on your bucket list. Speaking of iconic addresses, we''ve got a few in Bengaluru that age even better. \ud83d\ude09 #BengaluruLiving #FindYourCornerHouse", "city_hint": "Bengaluru", "tags": ["celebrity", "bengaluru", "viral", "luxury"]}','{"media_format": "meme_overlay", "meme_concept": "Use the viral paparazzi photo/clip of Narayana Murthy enjoying ice cream with Akshata Murty at Corner House Bengaluru. Overlay text bottom-center: ''Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? \ud83c\udf66\ud83c\udfe1''", "card_text": "Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? \ud83c\udf66\ud83c\udfe1", "trend_hashtag": "#NarayanaMurthy", "city_hint": "bengaluru", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/bengaluru", "alt_text": "Meme overlay image referencing Narayana Murthy''s viral Corner House ice cream visit, with text: ''Murthy sir Corner House gaye. Tum apna corner Bengaluru mein kab loge? \ud83c\udf66\ud83c\udfe1'' and Housing.com branding linking to Bengaluru property listings."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/c1c24586/instagram_a1f3c2d4_meme_placeholder.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(188,'8efb8026-f174-4c65-b738-7aa70d143d07','d91edf2b','twitter','dry_run_8efb8026','dry_run','output/d91edf2b/published/twitter_8efb8026.md','2026-05-19 02:27:35.687207',replace('Splitsvilla waale safe space dhundh rahe hain, aur tum abhi bhi PG mein ho 💀\n\nReal safe space mili toh batana. https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai','\n',char(10)),'["#SplitsvillaX6", "#MumbaiHomes", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "anchor_text": "mumbai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Splitsvilla safety drama → your ghar should be the one space that never feels unsafe. Gated societies with verified security on Housing.com.',1,0.0,7.0,0.0,5.099999999999999645,18500,142,38,52,2.100000000000000088,1.350000000000000088,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho 🏠🔒','\n',char(10)),'#SplitsvillaX6','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Splitsvilla X6 finale: Kashish Kapoor slams Niharika Tiwari for mocking Preet Singh over assault incident; says, “This is shaming the victim”.','The post opens with a clever enough wordplay on ''safe space'' from Splitsvilla, but immediately abandons the trend in line two and pivots into a housing feature list — ''gated societies, 24/7 security, verified reviews.'' That second line is pure product copy, and it completely kills the momentum of the hook. Compare this to the approved Ghibli AI example: ''Housing.com tumhara address badlega — that''s the real glow-up'' — the trend stays alive all the way through the punchline. Here, the trend is used as a door that gets slammed shut the moment you walk in. The result is that the post reads like a promo with a Splitsvilla disguise, not a Splitsvilla tweet with a Housing.com punchline. The two emojis (🏠🔒) are within limit but 🔒 feels like a security-feature icon rather than wit. Nobody is going to RT ''gated societies, 24/7 security, verified reviews'' — that''s brochure language, not Twitter language. The hashtag order is also wrong: #SplitsvillaX6 should lead, but the trend hook is so diluted by the body copy that even fixing the hashtags won''t rescue the post.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 4.5, "shareability": 4.0, "hinglish_wit": 5.0, "cta_quality": 7.0}','Strong hook leveraging pop-culture relevance (Splitsville X6 is trending among young audiences). The wit-based opening (''TV pe safe space dhundho band karo'') creates curiosity and stops scroll effectively. Emotional appeal (safety, security) resonates with homebuyers. However, engagement is capped by: (1) No visual asset — Twitter real estate content performs 40-60% better with property images/videos, (2) Hashtag #SplitsvillaX6 may dilute focus from core housing intent, (3) CTA is implicit (link only) rather than explicit. Relevance is strong if Splitsville X6 is actively trending; otherwise drops to 0.9%. Mumbai-specific targeting is smart for local engagement.','{"hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Splitsvilla X6 finale controversy as Kashish Kapoor calls out Niharika Tiwari for victim-shaming Preet Singh over a Mumbai club assault incident", "creative_hook": "Some spaces make you feel unsafe. Your HOME shouldn''t be one of them. \ud83c\udfe0 At Housing.com, we help you find gated communities with 24/7 security \u2014 because your safe space starts at home. #SplitsvillaX6 #SafeHome", "city_hint": "Mumbai", "tags": ["bollywood", "viral", "mumbai", "celebrity"]}','{"main_tweet": "TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhna band karo \ud83c\udfe0\ud83d\udd12\n\nMumbai mein ek actually safe ghar dhundho \u2014 gated societies, 24/7 security, verified reviews.\n\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "wit", "char_count": 170, "include_image": false, "revision_summary": "Kept the Splitsvilla safe-space hook as the punchline engine, cut all brochure copy, replaced \ud83d\udd12 with \ud83d\udc80 for drama, and moved #SplitsvillaX6 to lead \u2014 trend stays alive through the closer.", "revised": true}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(189,'30745b8b-6d1c-4243-931a-09cd3257f064','d91edf2b','instagram','dry_run_30745b8b','dry_run','output/d91edf2b/published/instagram_30745b8b.md','2026-05-19 02:27:35.698140','Splitsvilla pe ''safe space'' dhundhte reh… ya Mumbai mein ek real safe ghar dhoondh? Gated societies, 24/7 security 🔒🏠 housing.com/in/buy/mumbai','["#SplitsvillaX6", "#HousingDotCom", "#GharKhojna", "#MumbaiHomes", "#SafeHome", "#GatedSociety", "#MumbaiRealEstate", "#HomeSafety", "#MumbaiLiving", "#ApartmentHunting", "#SecureHomes", "#SplitsvillaX6Finale", "#MumbaiFlats", "#GharMilaKya", "#SafeGhar", "#MumbaiLife", "#NewHome2025"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "anchor_text": "mumbai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "caption"}]','["https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/d91edf2b/instagram_splitsvi.png"]','Splitsvilla safety drama → your ghar should be the one space that never feels unsafe. Gated societies with verified security on Housing.com.',1,0.0,0.0,0.0,6.299999999999999823,45000,1890,405,675,4.200000000000000177,6.799999999999999823,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho 🏠🔒','\n',char(10)),'#SplitsvillaX6','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Splitsvilla X6 finale: Kashish Kapoor slams Niharika Tiwari for mocking Preet Singh over assault incident; says, “This is shaming the victim”.','The card concept is functional but not scroll-stopping — the ''TV pe safe space vs real safe ghar'' parallel is a decent pun but it''s a one-note joke that doesn''t surprise. Compare to the Antilla meme overlay, which earns its laugh through contrast and specificity (27 floors, 2000 staff vs your 2 BHK). Here, the Splitsvilla hook is surface-level — ''safe space'' is a Splitsvilla term but the wordplay doesn''t land with enough wit to make someone DM it. The split-screen visual concept is solid but generic (dramatic scene vs serene society is predictable). The caption ''Splitsvilla pe safe space dhundhte reh… ya Mumbai mein ek real safe ghar dhoondh?'' essentially repeats the card text verbatim — card and caption are not designed as a unit, they''re the same idea said twice. The caption also runs long and the CTA ''Gated societies, 24/7 security 🔒🏠'' reads like a feature list, not a kicker. Hashtag count (17) is within range and trend tag is correctly first.','{"card_hook_strength": 6.5, "trend_and_shareability": 6.0, "caption_punch": 5.5, "hashtag_strategy": 8.0}','Strong hook leveraging Splitsvilla X6 finale trend (currently viral in India) with clever juxtaposition of TV drama vs. real-life safety concern. Hindi-English mix resonates with Mumbai demographic. Emotional trigger (safety/security) + aspiration (gated society living) + mild humour creates multi-layer appeal. Visual split-screen concept is visually arresting. However, confidence capped at 0.78 because: (1) trend relevance depends on exact timing relative to Splitsvilla finale broadcast, (2) branded card format slightly less organic than user-generated content, (3) CTA is indirect (link in caption rather than prominent button). The safety angle is evergreen but ''safe space'' discourse may feel slightly forced as a bridge to real estate.','{"hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Splitsvilla X6 finale controversy as Kashish Kapoor calls out Niharika Tiwari for victim-shaming Preet Singh over a Mumbai club assault incident", "creative_hook": "Some spaces make you feel unsafe. Your HOME shouldn''t be one of them. \ud83c\udfe0 At Housing.com, we help you find gated communities with 24/7 security \u2014 because your safe space starts at home. #SplitsvillaX6 #SafeHome", "city_hint": "Mumbai", "tags": ["bollywood", "viral", "mumbai", "celebrity"]}','{"media_format": "branded_card", "meme_concept": "", "card_text": "TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho \ud83c\udfe0\ud83d\udd12", "trend_hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "city_hint": "mumbai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "alt_text": "Branded card with a split-screen visual: left side shows a dramatic Splitsvilla safety controversy scene, right side shows a serene Mumbai gated society exterior at night with security lights. Bold Hindi overlay text reads ''TV pe safe space dhundhne se accha, Mumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho'' with a house and lock emoji. Housing.com logo and Mumbai city link displayed at the bottom."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/d91edf2b/instagram_splitsvi.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(190,'b7dc4527-8f60-4676-bb8e-e9c7ad3e90d8','d91edf2b','twitter','dry_run_b7dc4527','dry_run','output/d91edf2b/published/twitter_b7dc4527.md','2026-05-19 02:27:35.700701',replace('Splitsvilla X6 mein sab ''safe space'' maang rahe hain, par koi toh ghar bhi dhundho yaar 😭🏠\n\nTumhara safe space = verified homes on Housing.com\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai','\n',char(10)),'["#SplitsvillaX6", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "anchor_text": "mumbai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Splitsvilla safety drama → your ghar should be the one space that never feels unsafe. Gated societies with verified security on Housing.com.',1,0.0,7.0,0.0,5.099999999999999645,18500,142,38,52,2.100000000000000088,1.350000000000000088,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho 🏠🔒','\n',char(10)),'#SplitsvillaX6','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Splitsvilla X6 finale: Kashish Kapoor slams Niharika Tiwari for mocking Preet Singh over assault incident; says, “This is shaming the victim”.','The Splitsvilla X6 hook is paper-thin. ''Safe space'' is a vague emotional concept borrowed from reality TV discourse, but the post immediately abandons the show''s actual drama, contestants, or a specific viral moment to pivot into a product feature list — ''Gated societies, 24/7 security, verified reviews.'' That second line is pure brochure copy and kills whatever wit the opener attempted. Compare to the approved RCB example: ''Ee Sala Cup Namdu! RCB ne 18 saal baad apna ghar jeet liya'' — the trend IS the joke, and the housing pivot (''Tum apna ghar kab jeeto ge?'') is a single punchy line, not a feature dump. Here, the trend is a thin wrapper discarded after line one. A GenZ viewer who loves Splitsvilla would not RT this — there''s no specific reference to a contestant, a fight, a meme moment, or a quote from the show. The ''safe space'' wordplay is the right instinct but it''s too generic to land. Two emojis are used correctly, and the Hinglish is natural enough, but the second sentence drags the voice into corporate territory.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 4.5, "shareability": 4.0, "hinglish_wit": 5.0, "cta_quality": 7.0}','Strong hook leveraging Splitsville X6 cultural moment (trending show reference) creates immediate relevance and curiosity. Hindi-English mix (''safe space'' wordplay) resonates with urban Mumbai audience. Emotion driver (safety + aspiration) is solid. However, engagement is capped at ~1.35% because: (1) No visual asset (image/video) — critical miss for real estate on Twitter; (2) CTA is generic link-drop, not conversational; (3) Hashtag #SplitsvillaX6 may dilute focus if show momentum is fading. The wit hook is clever but relies on audience catching the reference.','{"hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Splitsvilla X6 finale controversy as Kashish Kapoor calls out Niharika Tiwari for victim-shaming Preet Singh over a Mumbai club assault incident", "creative_hook": "Some spaces make you feel unsafe. Your HOME shouldn''t be one of them. \ud83c\udfe0 At Housing.com, we help you find gated communities with 24/7 security \u2014 because your safe space starts at home. #SplitsvillaX6 #SafeHome", "city_hint": "Mumbai", "tags": ["bollywood", "viral", "mumbai", "celebrity"]}','{"main_tweet": "TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha, Mumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho \ud83c\udfe0\ud83d\udd12\n\nGated societies, 24/7 security, verified reviews \u2014 sab ek jagah.\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "wit", "char_count": 173, "include_image": false, "revision_summary": "Replaced the generic ''safe space'' opener with a direct Splitsvilla X6 contestant behaviour reference for fan recognition, cut the feature list entirely, and reduced the housing pivot to one punchy line anchored in the same wordplay.", "revised": true}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(191,'64b1c06f-4024-4b44-ae9e-7f72c9dc8037','d91edf2b','instagram','dry_run_64b1c06f','dry_run','output/d91edf2b/published/instagram_64b1c06f.md','2026-05-19 02:27:35.702388','Splitsvilla wala ''safe space'' nahi chahiye — chahiye ek asli safe ghar 🏠🔒 Gated societies, verified security. Mumbai mein dhundho: housing.com/in/buy/mumbai','["#SplitsvillaX6", "#HousingDotCom", "#GharKhojna", "#MumbaiHomes", "#SafeHome", "#MumbaiRealEstate", "#GatedCommunity", "#MumbaiLiving", "#ApnaGhar", "#HomeSafety", "#MumbaiFlats", "#GharDhundho", "#SecureHome", "#Splitsvilla", "#MumbaiLife", "#NewHome2025", "#PropertyMumbai"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "anchor_text": "mumbai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "caption"}]','["https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/d91edf2b/instagram_splitsvi.png"]','Splitsvilla safety drama → your ghar should be the one space that never feels unsafe. Gated societies with verified security on Housing.com.',1,0.0,0.0,0.0,6.5,45000,2100,380,520,4.200000000000000177,6.799999999999999823,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho 🏠🔒','\n',char(10)),'#SplitsvillaX6','branded_card','publish','published','[]','Splitsvilla X6 finale: Kashish Kapoor slams Niharika Tiwari for mocking Preet Singh over assault incident; says, “This is shaming the victim”.','The Splitsvilla angle is a decent trend-jack but the wordplay is surface-level — ''safe space'' as a pun connecting reality TV drama to home security is clever in concept but the execution feels mechanical. The card text ''TV pe safe space dhundhne se accha, Mumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho'' lands the joke but doesn''t surprise — it''s the most obvious version of this idea. Compare to the Antilla meme (approved benchmark): that card had a concrete, visual, almost absurd contrast (27 floors, 2000 staff → your 2 BHK) that made the pivot feel earned and funny. Here, the pivot from ''Splitsvilla drama'' to ''gated security'' is logical but not witty enough to make a non-house-hunter save or DM-forward it. The caption ''Splitsvilla wala safe space nahi chahiye — chahiye ek asli safe ghar'' essentially repeats the card text rather than closing it with a kicker — it''s the same joke told twice. The visual split-screen concept (chaotic TV left, calm gated society right) is solid but again the most predictable execution of this idea. Hashtag count (17) is within range and trend tag is correctly first.','{"card_hook_strength": 6.5, "trend_and_shareability": 6.0, "caption_punch": 6.5, "hashtag_strategy": 7.5}','Strong hook leveraging Splitsvilla''s massive cultural relevance in India (trending reality show with young, aspirational audience). The contrast between chaotic TV drama and calm home security creates immediate visual interest. Emotional appeal combines humour + aspiration + safety concerns (resonates with urban Mumbai audience). Hashtag strategy is robust with 16 tags including trending #SplitsvillaX6. Direct CTA with city-specific link reduces friction. However, confidence capped at 0.78 because: (1) branded cards sometimes underperform vs. organic reels, (2) Splitsvilla trend may have regional concentration, (3) safety messaging is functional rather than deeply emotional. The 6.8% predicted engagement rate sits in ''Good'' benchmark range for Housing.com.','{"hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Splitsvilla X6 finale controversy as Kashish Kapoor calls out Niharika Tiwari for victim-shaming Preet Singh over a Mumbai club assault incident", "creative_hook": "Some spaces make you feel unsafe. Your HOME shouldn''t be one of them. \ud83c\udfe0 At Housing.com, we help you find gated communities with 24/7 security \u2014 because your safe space starts at home. #SplitsvillaX6 #SafeHome", "city_hint": "Mumbai", "tags": ["bollywood", "viral", "mumbai", "celebrity"]}','{"media_format": "branded_card", "meme_concept": "", "card_text": "TV pe ''safe space'' dhundhne se accha,\nMumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho \ud83c\udfe0\ud83d\udd12", "trend_hashtag": "#SplitsvillaX6", "city_hint": "mumbai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "alt_text": "Branded card with a split design: left side shows a chaotic dramatic TV reality show scene (referencing Splitsvilla), right side shows a calm, well-lit gated residential society in Mumbai at night with security lights. Overlay text reads: ''TV pe safe space dhundhne se accha, Mumbai mein ek safe ghar dhundho \ud83c\udfe0\ud83d\udd12''. Housing.com logo and URL visible at the bottom."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/d91edf2b/instagram_splitsvi.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(192,'c195d7e9-6e99-4781-ab4b-7ee2f4d16108','d91edf2b','twitter','','','output/d91edf2b/rejected/twitter_c195d7e9.md','2026-05-19 02:27:35.703725',replace('Vibes pe ghar mat lo.\nVerified safety ratings pe lo. ✅\n\nSociety reviews, safety scores, real resident feedback — sab @HousingDotCom pe.\n\nMumbai mein dekho: https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai','\n',char(10)),'["#VictimShaming", "#SafeNeighbourhood", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "anchor_text": "mumbai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Anti-victim-shaming = pro-accountability = pro-transparency. Housing.com ke verified safety scores aur reviews = no guesswork, only data.',1,0.0,7.0,0.0,2.899999999999999912,8500,52,18,24,2.100000000000000088,1.300000000000000044,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Vibes pe ghar mat lo.\nVerified safety ratings pe lo. ✅🔐','\n',char(10)),'#VictimShaming','branded_card','reject','qa_rejected','["trend_dominance", "shareability", "Improve: #VictimShaming hashtag is a critical liability. It''s contextually inappropriate for a safety/housing message and signals tone-deaf messaging. Likely to trigger negative sentiment, reduce algorithmic amplification, and invite criticism. Recommend replacing with #SmartHousingChoices or #SafetyFirst. Absence of visual (society photo, safety badge, or comparison graphic) also reduces engagement by ~25-30%."]','Splitsvilla X6 finale: Kashish Kapoor slams Niharika Tiwari for mocking Preet Singh over assault incident; says, “This is shaming the victim”.','The most critical failure here is the hashtag #VictimShaming — this post is attempting to trend-jack a sensitive, likely crime/assault-related conversation by pivoting to ''safety ratings.'' That is not trend-jacking; that is brand opportunism on a trauma topic, which is reputationally dangerous and tone-deaf. Beyond the ethical red flag, there is zero trend hook in the copy itself — ''Vibes pe ghar mat lo'' is a standalone housing message with no cultural moment, no meme, no event, no trending conversation anchoring it. The hashtag is the only signal of a trend, and it''s the wrong one to attach to. Removing the housing.com link leaves nothing culturally resonant — just a generic safety pitch. Compared to approved examples like the RCB cup post or the Ghibli AI post, where the trend IS the joke and housing is the punchline, this post leads with the product message and uses a sensitive social issue as a thin, exploitative wrapper. ''Verified safety ratings pe lo'' reads like a feature ad, not a witty cultural observation. The Hinglish is functional but not sharp — there''s no wordplay, no twist, no moment of delight.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 1.0, "shareability": 2.0, "hinglish_wit": 4.0, "cta_quality": 7.0}','Strong hook (''Vibes pe ghar mat lo'') with relatable Hindi-English mix stops scroll effectively. Safety is a high-intent topic for Indian homebuyers, especially in metros. However, #VictimShaming hashtag is misaligned and creates negative association—this significantly dampens reach and sentiment. The CTA is clear but generic. No visual asset limits engagement potential. Relevance is evergreen but not trending. Emotion (aspiration + safety concern) is present but underutilized. Expected to perform above baseline (0.8%) but below ''good'' threshold (2-4%) due to hashtag liability.','{"hashtag": "#VictimShaming", "volume": "rising", "platform": "twitter", "context": "Kashish Kapoor''s powerful statement against victim-shaming at the Splitsvilla X6 finale goes viral, triggering conversations about safety and accountability", "creative_hook": "No one should be shamed for feeling unsafe \u2014 on TV or in their own colony. \ud83d\udd10 Housing.com listings now show safety scores, security ratings & neighbourhood reviews. Find a home where YOU set the standard. #VictimShaming #SafeNeighbourhood", "city_hint": null, "tags": ["viral", "celebrity", "mumbai", "bollywood"]}','{"main_tweet": "Vibes pe ghar mat lo.\nVerified safety ratings pe lo. \u2705\n\nSociety reviews, safety scores, real resident feedback \u2014 sab @HousingDotCom pe.\n\nMumbai mein dekho: https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "hot_take", "char_count": 189, "include_image": false}',NULL);
