d for feeling unsafe \u2014 on TV or in their own colony. \ud83d\udd10 Housing.com listings now show safety scores, security ratings & neighbourhood reviews. Find a home where YOU set the standard. #VictimShaming #SafeNeighbourhood", "city_hint": null, "tags": ["viral", "celebrity", "mumbai", "bollywood"]}','{"media_format": "branded_card", "meme_concept": "", "card_text": "Vibes pe ghar mat lo.\nVerified safety ratings pe lo. \u2705\ud83d\udd10", "trend_hashtag": "#VictimShaming", "city_hint": "mumbai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "alt_text": "Branded card with bold overlay text reading ''Vibes pe ghar mat lo. Verified safety ratings pe lo.'' against a Housing.com branded background. Visual emphasizes verified safety scores and resident reviews for Mumbai properties."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/d91edf2b/instagram_victim-s.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(196,'4d2dd6c6-56fb-44ba-b188-59642b52b782','8c103b6b','twitter','dry_run_4d2dd6c6','dry_run','output/8c103b6b/published/twitter_4d2dd6c6.md','2026-05-19 02:27:39.834757',replace('Fit nahi the, phir bhi ghar aaye. 💛\nThala ko ghar ka matlab pata hai.\nApna Chennai wala ghar dhundo 👉 housing.com/in/buy/chennai @msdhoni @ChennaiIPL','\n',char(10)),'["#MSDhoni", "#Thala", "#WhistlePodu", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "anchor_text": "chennai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Dhoni''s emotional return to Chepauk despite not being fully fit — ''ghar ke liye kuch bhi''. The stadium is his ghar; we sell the literal version.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,7.900000000000000355,45000,720,180,135,2.799999999999999823,2.450000000000000177,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Fit nahi the, phir bhi ghar aaye. 💛\nThala ko ghar ka matlab pata hai.','\n',char(10)),'#MSDhoni','meme_overlay','publish','published','[]','Suresh Raina has arrived at Chepauk as fans emotionally prepare for what could possibly be MS Dhoni''s final match for Chennai Super Kings against SRH.','This is a solid, emotionally resonant post that rides the Dhoni-returning-to-Chennai moment well. ''Fit nahi the, phir bhi ghar aaye'' is a genuinely sharp line — it captures the fan sentiment around Dhoni''s fitness concerns and his loyalty to CSK/Chennai in one breath, and the ''ghar'' double meaning (home ground + actual home) is the kind of wordplay Housing.com should be doing. The second line ''Thala ko ghar ka matlab pata hai'' lands the pivot cleanly. However, the third line ''Apna Chennai wala ghar dhundo'' is where the post loses a little steam — it''s a functional CTA but slightly generic, and ''Chennai wala ghar dhundo'' reads a touch like the ''AVOID THIS'' pattern of a bolted-on CTA. The emotional peak is lines 1-2; line 3 deflates it slightly. Compared to the approved RCB example (''Tum apna ghar kab jeeto ge?''), that CTA had a direct emotional mirror to the trend hook — here the CTA doesn''t quite carry the same Dhoni/Thala energy forward. Still, the trend is clearly dominant, the Hinglish is natural, and the post earns its place.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 8.0, "shareability": 7.5, "hinglish_wit": 7.5, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong nostalgia hook leveraging MSD''s injury comeback narrative (''Fit nahi the, phir bhi ghar aaye'') creates immediate emotional resonance with cricket fans. The ''Thala'' reference and Chennai connection tap into CSK''s passionate fanbase. However, engagement is capped by: (1) lack of visual asset (no image/video reduces stop-scroll power), (2) direct brand CTA feels slightly forced within emotional narrative, (3) relevance depends on current cricket season timing. The Hindi-English mix and emoji usage align well with Housing.com''s audience, but the connection between injury comeback and home-buying feels tangential rather than organic.','{"hashtag": "#MSDhoni", "volume": "high", "platform": "twitter", "context": "MS Dhoni arrives at Chepauk despite not being fully fit, sparking massive emotional reactions across India as fans brace for his possible last appearance in yellow.", "creative_hook": "Not fit to play, but still showed up for his home. \ud83e\udde4\ud83d\udc9b That''s Dhoni. That''s Chennai. Ghar ke liye kuch bhi. Because home isn''t just a place \u2014 it''s where you always return. Find your forever home on Housing.com. #MSDhoni #Thala", "city_hint": "Chennai", "tags": ["cricket", "ipl", "chennai", "sports", "viral"]}','{"main_tweet": "Fit nahi the, phir bhi ghar aaye. \ud83d\udc9b\nThala ko ghar ka matlab pata hai.\nApna Chennai wala ghar dhundo \ud83d\udc49 housing.com/in/buy/chennai @msdhoni @ChennaiIPL", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "nostalgia", "char_count": 149, "include_image": false}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(197,'57500a3b-b9f3-49a6-87b3-4d985eec419e','8c103b6b','twitter','dry_run_57500a3b','dry_run','output/8c103b6b/published/twitter_57500a3b.md','2026-05-19 02:27:39.839385',replace('Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛\n\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.\n\nApna wala Chennai dhundh lo 👉 housing.com/in/buy/chennai','\n',char(10)),'["#SureshRaina", "#MrIPL", "#CSK", "#Chennai"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "anchor_text": "chennai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Raina officially retired, lives elsewhere — but Chepauk still pulls him back. Same way your hometown/dream neighbourhood keeps calling, no matter where life takes you.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,8.800000000000000711,45000,520,180,95,2.799999999999999823,1.899999999999999912,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.','\n',char(10)),'#SureshRaina','meme_overlay','publish','published','[]','Suresh Raina has arrived at Chepauk as fans emotionally prepare for what could possibly be MS Dhoni''s final match for Chennai Super Kings against SRH.','This is a genuinely strong post. The Raina-Chepauk nostalgia hook is the entire soul of the tweet — ''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya'' lands emotionally before Housing.com even enters the picture. The pivot line ''Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte'' is the real gem — it does double duty as a cricket sentiment AND a housing metaphor without feeling forced. That''s exactly the kind of wordplay the format demands. The CTA ''Apna wala Chennai dhundh lo'' mirrors the emotional register of the hook (''apna wala'' echoes the belonging theme) rather than breaking the spell. Two emojis, clean Hinglish, no corporate stiffness. The only minor friction: ''Chepauk ne bula hi liya'' assumes the reader knows Raina''s Chepauk connection — which any CSK fan will, but it slightly narrows the universe of people who''ll feel the full punch. Still, for the hashtag audience (#MrIPL, #CSK), this is pitch-perfect. Scores marginally below a 9+ on shareability only because the emotional payoff is niche-cricket rather than universally relatable like the RCB cup win example.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 9.0, "shareability": 8.5, "hinglish_wit": 9.0, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong nostalgia hook leveraging Suresh Raina''s emotional connection to CSK/Chennai (retirement narrative). Hindi-English mix resonates with core Indian audience. Metaphor ''addresses that don''t fade'' cleverly bridges cricket sentiment to real estate. However, engagement limited by: (1) No visual asset (image/video would boost 30-40%), (2) CTA feels slightly forced—real estate pivot from cricket sentiment may create cognitive friction, (3) Hashtags are cricket-heavy but audience skew may be sports fans, not property seekers. Relevance is moderate—Raina''s retirement news is ~2 years old; freshness factor diminished unless tied to recent CSK event.','{"hashtag": "#SureshRaina", "volume": "rising", "platform": "instagram", "context": "Suresh Raina''s emotional return to Chepauk to support Dhoni is going viral, with fans calling it the most nostalgic IPL moment in years.", "creative_hook": "Raina left, but Chepauk never left his heart. \ud83e\udd79\ud83d\udc9b Mr. IPL phir aa gaya apne ghar. Because some homes are more than just walls \u2014 they''re your identity. Apna IPL moment find karo Housing.com pe. #SureshRaina #WhistlePodu", "city_hint": "Chennai", "tags": ["cricket", "ipl", "chennai", "sports", "viral", "celebrity"]}','{"main_tweet": "Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. \ud83d\udc9b\n\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.\n\nApna wala Chennai dhundh lo \ud83d\udc49 housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "nostalgia", "char_count": 165, "include_image": false}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(198,'31f0186d-ddfb-4eea-88e9-0398d4b1853d','8c103b6b','instagram','dry_run_31f0186d','dry_run','output/8c103b6b/published/instagram_31f0186d.md','2026-05-19 02:27:39.843857','Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛 Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte. Apna dhundho 👉 housing.com/in/buy/chennai','["#SureshRaina", "#HousingDotCom", "#GharKhojna", "#ChepauckCries", "#MrIPL", "#CSK", "#Chennai", "#ChennaiHomes", "#IPL2025", "#Chepauk", "#GharWapsi", "#DilKiProperty", "#ChennaiRealEstate", "#ApnaGhar", "#HomeSweetHome", "#NostalgiHit", "#BuyInChennai"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "anchor_text": "chennai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "caption"}]','["https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/8c103b6b/instagram_b7e2d9f1_meme_placeholder.png"]','Raina officially retired, lives elsewhere — but Chepauk still pulls him back. Same way your hometown/dream neighbourhood keeps calling, no matter where life takes you.',1,0.0,0.0,0.0,8.099999999999999645,185000,8880,2775,3330,4.799999999999999823,8.5,0.8199999999999999512,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.','\n',char(10)),'#SureshRaina','meme_overlay','publish','published','[]','Suresh Raina has arrived at Chepauk as fans emotionally prepare for what could possibly be MS Dhoni''s final match for Chennai Super Kings against SRH.','This is a genuinely strong post — the card text is emotionally layered and the wordplay on ''address'' (Chepauk as an address you can''t forget → find your own address) is the kind of organic pivot that separates good trend-jacking from bolted-on CTA. ''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya.'' lands like a three-act mini-story, which is rare for card copy. The housing pivot via ''Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte'' is clever and earns its place. Minor weaknesses: the caption largely repeats the card text verbatim (''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛 Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.'') before adding the CTA — card and caption feel like one idea copy-pasted rather than designed as a unit where the caption *closes* what the card *opened*. The caption should be a punchy kicker that adds a new beat, not a replay. Hashtag count is 17 (within range), trend tag #SureshRaina is correctly first, branded tags #HousingDotCom and #GharKhojna are present — solid. Minor dock: #NostalgiHit is a typo (#NostalgiaHit) and #ChepauckCries misspells Chepauk, which could hurt discoverability on a trending tag.','{"card_hook_strength": 8.5, "trend_and_shareability": 8.5, "caption_punch": 7.5, "hashtag_strategy": 7.5}','Strong hook leveraging real-time Suresh Raina nostalgia + Chepauk emotional connection (IPL 2025 context = fresh trend). Bilingual wordplay (''Retire ho gaya...Chepauk ne bula hi liya'') creates high curiosity & relatability for Hindi/Tamil audiences. Meme format + stadium imagery = scroll-stopping visual. Emotional resonance (homecoming, belonging) drives saves & shares. However, CTA is slightly indirect (link in caption vs. on-image), and property relevance feels tangential to cricket sentiment—may limit conversion intent. Hashtag density is strong but #SureshRaina dominance could overshadow #BuyInChennai reach.','{"hashtag": "#SureshRaina", "volume": "rising", "platform": "instagram", "context": "Suresh Raina''s emotional return to Chepauk to support Dhoni is going viral, with fans calling it the most nostalgic IPL moment in years.", "creative_hook": "Raina left, but Chepauk never left his heart. \ud83e\udd79\ud83d\udc9b Mr. IPL phir aa gaya apne ghar. Because some homes are more than just walls \u2014 they''re your identity. Apna IPL moment find karo Housing.com pe. #SureshRaina #WhistlePodu", "city_hint": "Chennai", "tags": ["cricket", "ipl", "chennai", "sports", "viral", "celebrity"]}','{"media_format": "meme_overlay", "meme_concept": "Use the viral clip/photo of Suresh Raina arriving at Chepauk stands today \u2014 emotional, waving to crowd, in civilian clothes. Overlay text bottom: ''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.''", "card_text": "Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. \ud83d\udc9b\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.", "trend_hashtag": "#SureshRaina", "city_hint": "chennai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "alt_text": "Meme overlay graphic with a warm yellow-tinted image of Chepauk stadium. Text reads: ''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. \ud83d\udc9b Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.'' Housing.com branding at the bottom with a Chennai property search CTA."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/8c103b6b/instagram_b7e2d9f1_meme_placeholder.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(199,'4036851f-3d92-4fdd-8c57-6ec8d6bf910d','8c103b6b','twitter','dry_run_4036851f','dry_run','output/8c103b6b/published/twitter_4036851f.md','2026-05-19 02:27:39.847842',replace('Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛\n\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.\n\nApna wala address dhundh rahe ho? housing.com/in/buy/chennai','\n',char(10)),'["#SureshRaina", "#MrIPL", "#CSK", "#Chennai"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "anchor_text": "chennai", "page_type": "city_srp", "placement": "tweet"}]','[]','Raina officially retired, lives elsewhere — but Chepauk still pulls him back. Same way your hometown/dream neighbourhood keeps calling, no matter where life takes you.',1,0.0,8.0,0.0,8.800000000000000711,45000,520,180,95,2.799999999999999823,1.899999999999999912,0.7199999999999999734,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. 💛\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.','\n',char(10)),'#SureshRaina','meme_overlay','publish','published','[]','Suresh Raina has arrived at Chepauk as fans emotionally prepare for what could possibly be MS Dhoni''s final match for Chennai Super Kings against SRH.','This is a genuinely strong post. The Raina-Chepauk nostalgia hook lands hard — ''Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya. Phir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya'' is emotionally resonant and culturally specific, tapping into the collective CSK fandom grief/joy around Raina''s relationship with Chennai. The pivot line ''Kuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte'' is the real gem — it does the heavy lifting of connecting the trend to housing without feeling forced, which is exactly the Housing.com playbook. The CTA is low-friction and city-specific. Minor quibble: the post uses only one emoji (💛), which is perfectly restrained, but the line break before the CTA question slightly softens the punchline momentum — it reads as two separate thoughts rather than one seamless flow. The shareability is high among CSK fans specifically, though slightly niche compared to broader IPL moments. Still, this matches or slightly edges the approved RCB example in emotional depth and wordplay tightness.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 9.0, "shareability": 8.5, "hinglish_wit": 9.0, "cta_quality": 8.0}','Strong nostalgia hook leveraging Suresh Raina''s iconic CSK retirement narrative—resonates deeply with cricket fans and Chennai loyalists. Hinglish execution is natural and relatable. Emotional connection (Chepauk calling back) creates aspiration. However, CTA feels slightly forced; the property angle isn''t seamlessly woven into the sentiment. Missing visual asset (image/video) limits viral potential. Hashtags are relevant but #SureshRaina may dilute focus if not trending. Predicted engagement sits in ''Good'' range (1.9% vs 0.8% baseline) but falls short of ''Viral'' due to weak CTA integration and lack of multimedia.','{"hashtag": "#SureshRaina", "volume": "rising", "platform": "instagram", "context": "Suresh Raina''s emotional return to Chepauk to support Dhoni is going viral, with fans calling it the most nostalgic IPL moment in years.", "creative_hook": "Raina left, but Chepauk never left his heart. \ud83e\udd79\ud83d\udc9b Mr. IPL phir aa gaya apne ghar. Because some homes are more than just walls \u2014 they''re your identity. Apna IPL moment find karo Housing.com pe. #SureshRaina #WhistlePodu", "city_hint": "Chennai", "tags": ["cricket", "ipl", "chennai", "sports", "viral", "celebrity"]}','{"main_tweet": "Retire ho gaya. Sheher chhod diya.\nPhir bhi Chepauk ne bula hi liya. \ud83d\udc9b\n\nKuch addresses bhulaye nahi bhulte.\n\nApna wala address dhundh rahe ho? housing.com/in/buy/chennai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "nostalgia", "char_count": 169, "include_image": false}',NULL);
