"tags": ["viral", "investment", "homeloan", "mumbai", "finance"]}','{"media_format": "branded_card", "meme_concept": "", "card_text": "Milan se Mumbai tak \u2014 NRIs ka dil bhi yahin, ghar bhi yahin \ud83c\uddee\ud83c\uddf3\ud83c\udfe1", "trend_hashtag": "#IndiaItalyRelations", "city_hint": "mumbai", "city_link": "https://housing.com/in/buy/mumbai", "alt_text": "Branded card with an India-Italy bilateral theme. Bold overlay text reads ''Milan se Mumbai tak \u2014 NRIs ka dil bhi yahin, ghar bhi yahin'' with Indian and Italian flag emojis. Housing.com branding visible. Background evokes a Milan-to-Mumbai visual journey."}','https://pub-f574a876869d4654b354fad0d657b289.r2.dev/housing-marketeer/6ce667d0/instagram_b2e3d4c5.png');
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(248,'0e3780f7-dc62-412e-a718-33cff1a6c9af','cebd2b8e','twitter','dry_run_0e3780f7','dry_run','output/cebd2b8e/draft/twitter_0e3780f7.md','2026-05-20 19:35:42.642885',replace('Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi 👀\n\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar.\n\nJob silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi. 🔑\nhttps://housing.com','\n',char(10)),'["#SilentLayoffs", "#ITLayoffs", "#JobSecurity", "#HousingDotCom"]','[]','[]','Silent layoffs hitting IT — your job can vanish quietly, but your ghar can''t. Pivot job anxiety into ownership pride.',1,0.0,6.0,0.0,4.900000000000000355,45000,520,180,95,2.799999999999999823,2.100000000000000088,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi 👀\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar 🔑','\n',char(10)),'#SilentLayoffs','branded_card','advisory','draft','[]','#SilentLayoffs','The post latches onto a real and resonant anxiety — silent layoffs, appraisal freezes, shrinking headcount — but it pivots too quickly and too earnestly into a housing pitch. By line 3 (''Ek cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar''), the trend has been abandoned and Housing.com is now the hero. Compare this to the approved RCB example: ''Ee Sala Cup Namdu! RCB ne 18 saal baad apna ghar jeet liya'' — the trend IS the whole joke, and housing is the punchline twist. Here, the trend is just a setup for a motivational real-estate message. The closing line ''Job silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi.'' is the strongest moment — it has rhythm and wordplay — but it arrives after the post has already shifted into promo mode, so it reads more like a tagline than a punchline. The tone also drifts slightly corporate-motivational (''Ek cheez apne naam kar lo'') rather than staying in the witty-friend register. A GenZ user experiencing layoff anxiety would feel slightly lectured at, not delighted — which kills shareability. The hook is real, the instinct is right, but the execution swaps the trend for a housing message too early.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 4.5, "shareability": 4.0, "hinglish_wit": 5.5, "cta_quality": 6.0}','Strong hook leveraging timely #SilentLayoffs trend (currently trending in Indian tech). Emotional resonance high — addresses job insecurity anxiety while pivoting to aspirational solution (home ownership as stability). Hindi-English mix increases relatability. Clever contrast (''Job silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi.'') creates memorable takeaway. However, CTA is weak (just link, no explicit action), and without visual asset, scroll-stopping power is reduced. Hashtags are relevant but #HousingDotCom feels self-promotional. Predicted engagement sits in ''Good'' range (2-4%) but unlikely to go viral without image/video.','{"hashtag": "#SilentLayoffs", "volume": "rising", "platform": "linkedin", "context": "50,000+ Indian IT jobs at risk through silent layoffs \u2014 no announcement, just shrinking teams and frozen appraisals.", "creative_hook": "Company ne kuch bola nahi. Appraisal bhi nahi aayi. Office mein seat bhi kum ho gayi. Yaar, ek cheez apne naam karo \u2014 apna ghar. Housing.com pe explore karo. \ud83d\udd11", "city_hint": null, "tags": ["layoffs", "linkedin", "workculture", "instability"]}','{"main_tweet": "Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi \ud83d\udc40\n\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo \u2014 apna ghar.\n\nJob silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi. \ud83d\udd11\nhttps://housing.com", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "hot_take", "char_count": 169, "include_image": false}',NULL);
INSERT INTO published_posts VALUES(249,'fa824ea8-a1f9-4046-a372-cc3a102880f9','cebd2b8e','twitter','dry_run_fa824ea8','dry_run','output/cebd2b8e/draft/twitter_fa824ea8.md','2026-05-20 19:35:43.240755',replace('Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi 👀\n\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar 🔑\n\nJob silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi.\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/real-estate-mumbai','\n',char(10)),'["#SilentLayoffs", "#ITLayoffs", "#JobSecurity", "#HousingDotCom"]','[{"url": "https://housing.com/in/buy/real-estate-mumbai", "anchor_text": "Properties in Mumbai", "page_type": "city_homepage", "city": "mumbai", "placement": "in the CTA"}]','[]','Silent layoffs hitting IT — your job can vanish quietly, but your ghar can''t. Pivot job anxiety into ownership pride.',1,0.0,7.0,0.0,5.799999999999999823,18500,285,156,94,2.799999999999999823,2.100000000000000088,0.7800000000000000266,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'social',replace('Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi 👀\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar 🔑','\n',char(10)),'#SilentLayoffs','branded_card','advisory','draft','[]','#SilentLayoffs','The post rides the #SilentLayoffs / #ITLayoffs anxiety wave, which is a real and resonant trend — but the execution makes Housing.com the main character, not the trend. The opening lines (''Company ne kuch bola nahi. Appraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi'') do capture the dread well, but the pivot — ''Ek cheez apne naam kar lo — apna ghar'' — immediately converts that anxiety into a real estate pitch, and the closing line ''Job silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi.'' is a brand slogan, not a cultural observation. Compare to the approved Ghibli example: ''AI ne tumhari photo badal di'' is the whole joke; housing is the punchline twist. Here, the trend is a setup for a sales message rather than the dominant hook. The result is that someone scrolling through #SilentLayoffs content would feel sold to, not seen — which kills shareability. A GenZ IT worker experiencing layoff anxiety is unlikely to RT this because it reads like a brand capitalising on their fear rather than genuinely reflecting it back. The two emojis are fine, Hinglish is natural, but the punchline (''Ghar nahi'') lands more like a tagline than a witty observation. It''s above the ''AVOID THIS'' floor but clearly below the approved examples in trend dominance and organic shareability.','{"character_compliance": 10.0, "trend_dominance": 5.5, "shareability": 5.0, "hinglish_wit": 6.0, "cta_quality": 7.0}','Strong hook leveraging current #SilentLayoffs trend (highly relevant in Jan 2025 IT sector context). Emotional resonance through relatable pain points (appraisal delays, seat cuts) creates immediate identification. The pivot to home ownership as stability anchor is aspirational and timely. Conversational Hindi-English mix increases accessibility. However, lacks visual asset (image/video) which would boost engagement by 30-40%. CTA is present but indirect—link placement could be stronger. Hashtags are trending but somewhat generic. The ''ghar nahi'' (home won''t fail you) messaging is powerful for risk-averse audience during economic uncertainty.','{"hashtag": "#SilentLayoffs", "volume": "rising", "platform": "linkedin", "context": "50,000+ Indian IT jobs at risk through silent layoffs \u2014 no announcement, just shrinking teams and frozen appraisals.", "creative_hook": "Company ne kuch bola nahi. Appraisal bhi nahi aayi. Office mein seat bhi kum ho gayi. Yaar, ek cheez apne naam karo \u2014 apna ghar. Housing.com pe explore karo. \ud83d\udd11", "city_hint": null, "tags": ["layoffs", "linkedin", "workculture", "instability"]}','{"main_tweet": "Company ne kuch bola nahi.\nAppraisal nahi aayi. Seat bhi kam ho gayi \ud83d\udc40\n\nEk cheez apne naam kar lo \u2014 apna ghar \ud83d\udd11\n\nJob silent ho sakti hai. Ghar nahi.\nhttps://housing.com/in/buy/real-estate-mumbai", "thread": [], "is_thread": false, "hook_type": "hot_take", "char_count": 194, "include_image": false}',NULL);
